      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>Coronafacic acid, a bacterial toxin, was synthesized using a key step that involves three sequential pericyclic reactions. Identify them, and propose a mechanism for the overall transformation. How would you complete the synthesis?</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBdjBaIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--562b01de1f5e551c23f31c068d3cbf626a95641c/OChem_30_EC_006.jpg\" alt=\"The reactant reacts with heat in the presence of 185 degree Celsius to give an intermediate. This reacts with an unknown reagent represented as question mark to form coronafacic acid.\">",
